      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HERBIE (7) jumped from a low draw and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 1.3 lengths (17.09) behind Truth Teller at Healesville. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from three attempts. Makes plenty of appeal. ATHENIAN GODDESS (1) used the rails draw to advantage to get home last time at Healesville over 300m (17.02) after being shuffled back early, scoring by half a length. Should be in this for a long way. URGING (8) turned in a plain effort last time when fifth at Sale over 435m behind Jovial Gem (25.36) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Can measure up this time. GOT IMMUNITY (4) is very honest and looms as a strong winning hope again.",
